dollars in damage. So far, at
least five people have

03:01.715 --> 03:05.952 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
died in storm-related accidents.

03:05.952 --> 03:10.791 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the day's other news, bad
weather off the Greek islands
caused one of the worst migrant

03:10.791 --> 03:16.663 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tragedies yet. At least 46
people, including 17 children,
drowned when two wooden boats

03:16.663 --> 03:21.968 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
capsized as they tried to cross
from Turkey. So far, dangerous
winter weather conditions

03:21.968 --> 03:26.039 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have not stopped the surge of
people trying to reach Europe by
boat. But the rising fatalities

03:26.039 --> 03:30.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
make this the deadliest
January on record.

03:30.744 --> 03:35.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The prime minister of Iraq now
says criminal gangs may have
abducted three Americans in

03:35.415 --> 03:39.886 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Baghdad for ransom. But he also
says it is not yet clear they
were kidnapped at all.

03:39.886 --> 03:43.523 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
