that's multiplying as quickly as
these cats are?

47:33.117 --> 47:35.386 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ADITHYA SAMBAMURTHY:
It's really difficult.

47:35.386 --> 47:41.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the one thing that I found
is that this is a largely
volunteer-driven effort. The

47:41.859 --> 47:46.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
movement to, you know, sterilize
these cats and put them back
outside is largely driven

47:46.697 --> 47:49.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
by volunteers, who are
incredibly hardworking. They
have jobs. They have families.
And they

47:49.500 --> 47:52.903 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
do this work.

47:52.903 --> 47:56.173 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Unfortunately, as I'm finding,
it's not proving to work at that
scale. It's just a really

47:56.173 --> 47:58.309 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
difficult endeavor.

47:58.309 --> 48:02.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Adithya
